Experience with childhood urolithiasis. Report of 196 cases.
 A total of 196 children with urinary calculi were treated surgically.
 Their ages ranged from 1 to 14 years.
 The male:female ratio was 3:1.
 Stones were located in the kidney in 96 patients, in the bladder in 52 and in the ureters in 32.
 Multiple organ involvement was present in 16 patients and associated urinary tract anomalies were found in 11.
 Stone analysis revealed calcium oxalate and phosphate stones in 121 patients, struvite stones in 60 and uric acid stones in 15.
